					   <td>

			
			
			



<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Player kicked for mentioning BBB?</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=531884" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>
Yesterday while reading through my lore e-mail, I came across a rather
disturbing sounding e-mail from a person who claimed to be kicked out from
chat for mentioning the BBB (Better Business Bureau).  Here is part of his letter
(his full e-mail was rather large):

<blockquote><font color=#CCAA99>
 Last night I went back into chat to try and get my main character unstuck. He's
been stuck since luclin came out and well I thouht I'd give them some time. I go into chat and of course was there for 30 minutes with
no acknowledgment. Another person in chat asked "Is there any one that will listen to my complaints?" I told him in general chat, not
a tell, that if he was unhappy with the service that is supposed to be provided to contact the BBB and file a complaint. BAM! I was
immediately booted from chat and locked out. On the off chance that I had lost connection of something and the timing had just
worked out, I decided to log on my other account and see what happened. I was in chat for 10-15 minutes and never got dropped. I
mentioned the BBB again and BAM! out I go, again locked out of chat.<br><br>
<a href='mailto:George@eaze.net'>Galandir Athelstan</a><br>
51 warrior ~ Salvation of Norrath<br>
The Tribunal
</font></blockquote>

In my past time assisting in the EQ CS side of things, I have never once heard
of a GM feeling it neccisary to kick someone out of chat for mentioning the 
BBB.  Although Verant has declined comment on this, I have found one other
person that mentioned something similar happening.<br><Br>

As part of my research looking into this, I came across the BBB's web site and
have found where anyone can freely review Verant (Sony Online Entertainment)'s
BBB report.  To read the full report from the BBB site, <a href='http://www.sandiego.bbb.org/report.html?compid=11000350&national=Y'>CLICK HERE</a>.</br><br>

This also may be a resource that those no longer able to play the game due
to operating system or hardware issues, or others that may feel that they have
been wronged may take as an alternative course of action, should direct 
communication not work.  You can fill out a complaint right on line by going
<a href='http://www.sandiego.bbb.org/complaint/'>HERE</a>.  However, it is
always a good idea to try to work out any problems with the company first
before seeking resolution through a 3rd party such as the BBB.
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
