				Straight from the BBB report for Verant. I've taken the liberty of putting the important information in all caps, for the trained monkeys like Zack who obviously can't read.<BR>
<BR>
Oh, and Zack, people have ALWAYS been free to find Verant's BBB record. Those records are public information that has ALWAYS been freely available. Dumbass. Trying to stir s%^t where there is none.<BR>
<BR>
On to the record:<BR>
<BR>
Customer Experience<BR>
<BR>
Consumer complaints received by the Bureau concern non-receipt of products and difficulty in using the game. The company responded to the Bureau in a letter dated April 16, 2001, indicating that they had trouble with a shipping company for a short time in April 2000, which is the same time in which the Bureau received most of the complaints alleging non-receipt of product. THE CONSUMERS WHO COMPLAINED WERE GIVEN COMPLETE REFUNDS. Since this short period of time in April 2000, THE COMPANY SEEMS TO HAVE ELIMINATED THIS PATTERN OF CONSUMER COMPLAINTS.<BR>
<BR>
Customer Complaint Information<BR>
The following data concern complaints processed by the BBB since the firm's BBB file was opened in April of 1999 or over the last 36 months, whichever is less.  <BR>
<BR>
Number of Complaints Processed by the BBB in Last 36 Months, or date file opened if less than 36 months: 64<BR>
<BR>
Number of Complaints Processed by the BBB in Last 12 Months: 17<BR>
<BR>
Complaints Concerning<BR>
   Selling Practices - 1<BR>
      Number in the last 12 months (0)<BR>
      Outcome of all complaints - COMPANY MADE EVERY REASONABLE ATTEMPT TO RESOLVE (1)  <BR>
   Delivery - 17<BR>
      Number in the last 12 months (0)<BR>
      Outcome of all complaints - RESOLVED(17)  <BR>
   Product Quality - 3<BR>
      Number in the last 12 months (0)<BR>
      Outcome of all complaints - RESOLVED (3)  <BR>
   Refund - 2<BR>
      Number in the last 12 months (1)<BR>
      Outcome of all complaints - RESOLVED (2)  <BR>
   Contract - 2<BR>
      Number in the last 12 months (1)<BR>
      Outcome of all complaints - RESOLVED (2)  <BR>
   Service - 32<BR>
      Number in the last 12 months (13)<BR>
      Outcome of all complaints - RESOLVED (29) <BR>
COMPANY MADE EVERY REASONABLE ATTEMPT TO RESOLVE (3)  <BR>
   Credit or Billing - 7<BR>
      Number in the last 12 months (2)<BR>
      Outcome of all complaints - RESOLVED (7)  <BR>
<BR>
Looky there....every complaint resolved or they tried their damndest to resolve them. They have, according to this report, a GOOD reputation as a business.<BR>
<BR>
Doesn't sound like an evil company to me. If they were, they wouldn't bother trying to do anything when people complained. They'd just let it go.<BR>
<BR>
I'll say it again-- Everlore is useless tabloid &quot;journalism&quot; now. I have yet to see anything useful, like new spells, or new quests, or any Luclin information. It seems this site would rather bash Verant than serve its readers with stuff that is relevant instead of this crap.<BR>
<BR>
And you're still a tool, Zack. <BR>
